                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: fine. Hand b: poor.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: ʿAśratä Māryām, Gabra
                           Śǝllāse. ʿAśratä Māryām (hand a) is mentioned as the scribe in
                        supplication formulas throughout Text I; possibly he is the scribe of
                        DMD-007.
 Gabra Śǝllāse (hand b) is mentioned as the scribe in the
                        supplication formula on <locus target="#71rb">71rb</locus> (Text
                           III).<date>Second half of the 19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
