                              ... </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The text is written in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz, with many scribal
                              errors, very crudely, right beneath Text III in hand b. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Däqiqä Ṣǝyon "Children of Zion" are mentioned together
                           with the name of the donor in some supplication formulas throughout Text
                           I-4 (<locus target="#12va">12va</locus>, 18ra, 20rb etc.).
 - Omitted
                           words inserted interlineally: <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>, 3vb, 7ra,
                           15ra, 28ra, 41vb.
 - Corrections written over erasures: <locus target="#8ra">8ra-</locus>rb, 9va, 35va, 37va, 69vb.
 - Erasures
                           marked with thin lines: <locus target="#5rb">5rb</locus>, 11ra, 35va,
                           62ra.
 - Cues for the rubricator: <locus target="#35rb">35rb</locus>,
                           50ra, 59va.
 - Small signs written throughout Text I, in the margins;
                           their function is not clear. 
 - Spaces for rubricated passages and
                           names left unfilled: <locus target="#63va">63va-</locus>vb.
 -
                           Scribbles and crude drawings: <locus target="#54vb">54vb</locus>, 59vb,
                           71v, 72rv.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
