               <provenance>The name of Ḍäḥayä Lǝda (cp. Ms. AP-022) is
                     written in supplication formulas throughout Text I, in hand a (7ra, 10rb, 11ra etc.). In addition, his relatives are
                     mentioned: his wife Walatta Muse (8rb, 11rb, 14ra
                     etc.), his son Gabra Ṣādǝq (12va, 35ra etc.), his
                     father Mazgaba Śǝllāse (21ra, 25ra, 33ra etc.)
                     and his mother Walatta ʾAragāwi (27rb, 33vb, 39va
                     etc.). 
 
 The name Ḫāyla Māryām is written in Additio 1, in hand b
                        (2r).</provenance></history>
